# Patch target: /etc/caddy/Caddyfile
# INSTALLED 2026-05-28 (this exact form is in production).
#
# Inside the existing `crmphone.merkazneshama.co.il { ... }` block, add the
# `handle /api/queue-actions*` directive *before* the catch-all
# `handle { reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8090 ... }` block, so it matches first.
#
# NOTE — use `handle`, not `handle_path`. `handle_path` strips the matched
# prefix before proxying; the sidecar's Express routes are mounted at the
# full `/api/queue-actions` path, so the request must arrive with the prefix
# intact. (Earlier draft of this patch used `handle_path` and produced 404s
# from Express; fixed in the same install session.)
#
# After applying, run: sudo caddy validate --config /etc/caddy/Caddyfile
# then:                sudo systemctl reload caddy

# --- begin patch (insert before the existing `handle { reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8090 ... }`) ---

	handle /api/queue-actions* {
		reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8211 {
			lb_try_duration 3s
			lb_try_interval 200ms
		}
	}

# --- end patch ---
